        <updateDate>2016-10-31T11:40:26Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Caring Recovery for Infants and Babies Act or the CRIB Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends title XIX (Medicaid) of the Social Security Act to allow a state Medicaid program to cover inpatient or outpatient&nbsp;services at a&nbsp;residential pediatric recovery center for infants with neonatal abstinence syndrome (a postnatal drug withdrawal syndrome) and their families.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
